---

## 5. Practical Implications

- **Player evaluation:** adjusted VBA provides a fairer comparison across hitters than raw averages by reducing pitch-environment bias  
- **Player development:** intrinsic VBA can serve as a mechanical benchmark to track swing changes over time (paired with batted-ball goals)  
- **Advance scouting:** pairing intrinsic VBA with opponent pitch profiles can help frame matchups (e.g., plane matching vs pitch shape/location trends)

